{
  "texts": [
    "We evaluate their predictive performance by assessing both predictive accuracy and computational costs.",
    "The R 2 values between the soil moisture predictions generated by the three models and the ground truth across 10 sites and 5 depths are presented in Table 3.",
    "Additionally, Fig. 9a -e display the average RMSE values for soil moisture predictions at 30 sites.",
    "The results reveal that the LSTM model achieves the highest prediction accuracy, followed by the 1D-CNN model and, subsequently, the Transformer model.",
    "Notably, LSTM and Transformer are more stable when making 7 d or deepsoil-moisture predictions, while 1D-CNN is better suited for short-term and shallow prediction tasks."
  ]
}